h3. Issue Summary

We have the option to customize exports of PDF and set a header and footer with custom content. If you insert an image-based example or either a long text, the content will be almost completely hidden by the content of the page.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new space.
 # Create a few pages and insert some content in them.
 # Under *Space Settings > Look and Feel > PDF Export Stylesheet* and insert the following:
{code:css}
.pagetitle
{
page-break-before: always;
}
@page
{
margin-top: 1in;
@top-left
{
background-image: url("/download/attachments/<CONTENTID>/logo.png");
background-repeat: no-repeat;
background-position: 10px 25px;
}
@top-right
{
background-image: url("/download/attachments/<CONTENTID>/address.png");
background-repeat: no-repeat;
background-position: 10px 25px;
}
@bottom-center
{
content: "FOOTER TEXT";
font-family: ConfluenceInstalledFont, Calibri, sans-serif;
font-size: 8pt;
}
}
{code}

 # Go to *Content Tools > Export*.
 # Export the space.
 # Done!

h3. Expected Results

The header of each page would include the content inserted.
h3. Actual Results

The header content is stripped out almost entirely. We can only see the tip of the image/text behind the PDF content.
h3. Workaround

None at the moment.

For Confluence Cloud, please create an option to hide the created by and last updated by fields. These data points suggest to many members of our organization that the users named in these fields were the primary contributors to the page, which is often not the case. This is especially problematic for the actual main contributors whose work is not only less visible but appears to have been done by someone else.

{color:#FF0000}This is discouraging participation, and that makes Confluence less valuable for our organization.{color}

In its current position at the top right of the page, this information is impossible to ignore. Please hide it by default or give the option to hide it.

h3. Summary
Undefined links should link pages other than title alone. When creating an undefined link, if the user clicks the undefined link and rename the newly created page the link to the original page will be lost (as pages must have the exact same name of the undefined link, otherwise no page will be associated with that link, even after creating a page from undefined link itself)

h3. Environment
* Old Editor
* Creating new pages from Undefined Links

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new page;
# Insert a link by typing "[" > click "Insert Web Link" > select *Advanced* on the left pane;
# On the field 'Link' add a name to the page, such as "Example" > Click *Insert*;
# This will create an undefined link to this "Example" page (Do not publish the page yet)
# Click this undefined link > This will create a new draft page with the title "Example";
# Modify the title of the page from "Example" to something else, such as "Ex ample" > Publish it;
# Navigate back to the original page with the undefined link.
# Click the undefined link;

h3. Actual Results
* A blank page with the original title ("Example") is created;.

h3. Expected Results
* Instead of creating a new page with the original title ("Example"), Confluence should instead link the page created with the edited title ("Ex ample") as this page was originally created from the undefined link present on the "parent" page.



 
h3. Notes
Confluence should link these pages based on another factor other than title alone, as a page created from an undefined link will not be linked to the original page, unless its title continues the same after its creation.

h3. Summary
"Jira Issue/Filter" macro does not update custom field name (after changing it in Jira), and removes the custom field from "Columns to display".


h3. Environment
* "Jira" Macro;
* Updating the custom field name, while there is a "Jira Issue/Filter" macro reporting on the old name of the custom field.


h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page and insert "Jira Issue/Filter" macro into it;
# Edit the macro > Click the *Display options* section in this macro > Insert a custom field into "Columns to display" (e.g. 'Test Custom field');
# Publish the page;
 !Screen Shot 2019-03-26 at 14.28.07.png|thumbnail! 
# Navigate to Jira > Edit the name of the custom field (from 'Test Custom field' to something else, like 'Edited Test Custom Field');


h3. Expected Results
* Custom field name to be updated on "Jira Issue/Filter" macro in Confluence;
* Macro to display updated custom field, with its value for each reported issue.

h3. Actual Results
 * Custom field name is not updated on "Jira Issue/Filter" macro.  
 * The old custom field name is still being displayed as a column, but it is empty for every on the list;
 !Screen Shot 2019-03-26 at 14.37.17.png|thumbnail! 
 * Editing the page > Editing "Jira Issue/Filter" macro > Neither Old custom field name ('Test Custom field'), nor the new one ('Edited Test Custom Field') are listed under "Columns to display";
* *Note*: One additional behavior is that sometimes even though adding the new field's name back to the macro and saving it results in the macro not saving this field, and not displaying it after publishing the page;

h3. Workaround
* Editing the macro > Clicking *Display options* > Adding the updated custom field name ('Edited Test Custom Field') > *Insert*
This workaround forces Confluence to update the macro to include the updated custom field.
* If the macro does not save the updated custom field name, the alternative would be removing the macro alltogether and readding it.
 !Screen Shot 2019-03-26 at 14.41.09.png|thumbnail!

h3. Summary

It would be great if there's an option to delete children along with the parent. Currently vendors use this API to delete:

{noformat}
DELETE /wiki/rest/api/content/{id}
{noformat}

h3. Background
From Devhelp:
{quote}
In our product, we have a requirement to delete all the child pages when the parent page is deleted (similar to confluence server).
{quote}

h3. Note

This can be done in Confluence server Java API
